Foreign; not native; extrinsic or from without; exotic. [Speltalso pelegrine.] "Peregrine and preternatural heat." Bacon. Peregrinefalcon (Zo√∂l.), a courageous and swift falcon (Falco peregrinus),remarkable for its wide distribution over all the continents. Theadult plumage is dark bluish ash on the back, nearly black on thehead and cheeks, white beneath, barred with black below the throat.Called also peregrine hawk, duck hawk, game hawk, and great-footedhawk.
